<subSubSection pageId="169" pageNumber="448" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="169.[2013,2606,1089,1512]" lastBlockId="169.[1399,2607,1518,2101]" pageId="169" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2013,2294,1439,1472]" pageId="169" pageNumber="448">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 182-290 mm, tail 191-270 mm, ear 17-24 mm, hindfoot 46-57 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. See general characters of the genus under the Trinidad Water Rat (N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen &amp; Chapman" authorityYear="1893" box="[2186,2300,1556,1589]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Nectomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="169" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palmipes">palmipes</taxonomicName>
) account. Dorsum of the Magdalena Water Ratis coarsely mixed grayish ocherous, mid-dorsal dark band is absent, and venter is ocherous gray whitish. Skull is robust and heavy, with frontal and parietal regions markedly swollen. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 32 for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1932" box="[2510,2607,1675,1708]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="169" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandis">grandis</taxonomicName>
and 2n = 34, FN = 40 for nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osgood" authorityYear="1909" box="[1966,2116,1722,1747]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Nectomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="169" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magdalenae">magdalenae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
